# Protected paths — single source of truth for the repo's agent guardrails.
#
# Consumed by: the git hooks (.githooks/), the CI `policy-guard` job, the Claude
# PreToolUse adapter (.claude/hooks/), the CODEOWNERS generator, and the
# critical-path notifier. Editing any path matched here is a deliberate, reviewed
# act — not routine work.
#
# Format, one rule per line:   <glob>  |  <owner>  |  <tier>  |  <reason>
#   - glob: gitignore-style; `**` spans directories, `*` stays within a segment.
#   - owner: GitHub handle that must review changes (flows into CODEOWNERS).
#   - tier: `critical` also fires a loud alert when the path changes (ADR 0012);
#           `review` is gated by code-owner review only. Blank/unknown = review.
#   - reason: why this is load-bearing.
# Blank lines and lines starting with `#` are ignored.
#
# Deliberately a flat list, not YAML: the enforcers are zero-dependency POSIX
# shell, so the policy must parse without a YAML library. See ADR 0010 (and ADR
# 0012 for why the non-load-bearing notifier may use a library).

tests/Harness/**          | @MgCohen | critical | Test harness: the enforcement engine (ParityGuard, Rule, TestTypes).
tests/Meta/**             | @MgCohen | critical | Meta tests that police the test taxonomy and parity.
tests/**/Rulebook/**      | @MgCohen | critical | Rulebooks: the guarantees each test type proves.
.github/**                | @MgCohen | critical | CI, CODEOWNERS, and repo workflow config — the server-side backstop.
.githooks/**              | @MgCohen | critical | Local git-hook enforcers.
governance/**             | @MgCohen | critical | The policy itself and its enforcers — cannot be quietly weakened.
.claude/settings.json     | @MgCohen | critical | Claude harness config, incl. the PreToolUse guard — cannot disable its own guard.
design/adr/**             | @MgCohen | review   | Architecture Decision Records — frozen history, not living docs.
CLAUDE.md                 | @MgCohen | review   | Agent operating instructions for this repo.
Directory.Build.props     | @MgCohen | review   | Solution-wide build config (nullable, warnings-as-errors, net10).
.editorconfig             | @MgCohen | review   | Mechanical style rules.
ABox.slnx                 | @MgCohen | review   | The one unified solution definition.
